### Unit Tests
- `epoll::tests::create_reactor` - Create EpollReactor
- `epoll::tests::register_fd` - Register with EPOLL_CTL_ADD
- `epoll::tests::reregister_fd` - Modify with EPOLL_CTL_MOD
- `epoll::tests::deregister_fd` - Remove with EPOLL_CTL_DEL
- `epoll::tests::poll_events` - epoll_wait returns events
- `epoll::tests::poll_timeout` - Timeout behavior
- `epoll::tests::edge_triggered` - EPOLLET mode
- `epoll::tests::level_triggered` - Default mode
- `epoll::tests::wake_via_eventfd` - Eventfd wake mechanism
- `epoll::tests::oneshot_mode` - EPOLLONESHOT behavior

### Integration Tests (Linux CI)
- `epoll::integration::tcp_listener` - Accept connections
- `epoll::integration::tcp_stream` - Read/write
- `epoll::integration::unix_socket` - Unix domain sockets
- `epoll::integration::with_io_driver` - Full IoDriver integration
- `epoll::integration::fallback_from_io_uring` - When io_uring unavailable

### Stress Tests
- `epoll::stress::many_fds` - 10000+ file descriptors
- `epoll::stress::rapid_events` - High event rate
- `epoll::stress::wake_storm` - Many concurrent wakes

### Logging Requirements
- TRACE: epoll_ctl calls, event details
- DEBUG: Poll results, registrations
- INFO: Reactor lifecycle
- WARN: Unexpected events, EPOLLHUP
- ERROR: Syscall failures with errno

